- Fees can be: withdrawn (bad), burned (good), held (neutral)
- Badge tiers based on burn percentage
- $ASDFASDFA is the reference "good" token (99%+ burns)

When writing components:
- Use Tailwind classes inline
- Extract repeated styles to components, not CSS
- Prefer composition over prop drilling
- Add aria labels for accessibility

When writing API routes:
- Validate inputs with zod
- Return consistent error format
- Cache expensive queries
- Log errors to console (Vercel captures)

When writing database queries:
- Always use Prisma client
- Include proper indexes in schema
- Handle not-found cases
- Use transactions for multi-step operations

